    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-07-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-09-02T19:37:44Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Closing the Coverage Gap Act of 2004 - Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act, as amended by the Medicare Prescription Drug, Improvement, and Modernization Act of 2003, to eliminate: (1) the initial standard prescription drug coverage limit of $2,250 (adjusted for inflation); and (2) the MedicareAdvantage regional plan stabilization fund.</p> <p>Repeals the Premium Support Demonstration Program.</p> <p>Eliminates Health Savings Accounts under the Medicare Prescription Drug, Improvement, and Modernization Act of 2003. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
